&lt;h1&gt;Speciality Doctor in Learning Disabilities Adult&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Black Country Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust is currently recruiting for a 0.8 Speciality Doctor in Learning Disabilities Adult on a substantive basis. The position will be working in the Dudley locality, in the West Midlands. The base will be at The Ridge Hill Centre, Brierley Hill Road, Nr Stourbridge DY8 5ST. The proposed start date is as soon as possible but 3 months notice will also be feasible. To be eligible for the role, you will need :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a GMC licence to practice in the UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum of 2 years working in Psychiatry&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At least 6 months employment in Learning Disabilities Psychiatry&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Section 12 approval is ideal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Dr Ansar Choudry, Clinical Director on 0121 612 8425&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or Dr Adam Kirby, Consultant Psychiatrist 0n 01384 323557&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Ansar ChoudryJob titleSpeciality Doctor in Learning Disabilities AdultTelephone number0121 612 8425Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Adam Kirby 01384 323557&lt;/p&gt;
